   <pb facs="4"/>
   <head>To his friend the Authour.</head>
   <l>THou art the World, and now methinks I see</l>
   <l>A world of goodnesse here distill'd from thee;</l>
   <l>Distill'd in lines so sweetly, I protest</l>
   <l>I thought thy book the crystall of thy breast:</l>
   <l>Where live Idea's, such as all shall passe</l>
   <l>When they endure; onely in clearnesse glasse.</l>
   <l>Yet now i'le blame thee: If thou would'st have had</l>
   <l>The world drawn right, some line should have been bad.</l>
   <closer>
      <signed>THO. HARLESTON, Coll. <hi>Pemb.</hi>
      </signed>
   </closer>
